# Superpowers workflow (Ramadan Tracker)

Uses the **Superpowers** Cursor plugin (enabled in `.cursor/settings.json`). A **user-level session hook** (`~/.cursor/hooks.json`) injects `using-superpowers` at chat start — no need to type `/using-superpowers`. Plugin skills override default agent behavior; **project rules and user instructions win** when they conflict (e.g. `git-require-approval`).

## Skill pipeline (do not skip)

| Order | Skill | Trigger |
|-------|-------|---------|
| 1 | `brainstorming` | New feature, behavior change, or non-trivial fix |
| 2 | `using-git-worktrees` | After approved design — isolate in `.worktrees/` |
| 3 | `writing-plans` | After approved design — bite-sized TDD tasks |
| 4 | `subagent-driven-development` or `executing-plans` | Implement the plan |
| 5 | `test-driven-development` | Every implementation task |
| 6 | `systematic-debugging` | Bug, test failure, or unexpected behavior |
| 7 | `verification-before-completion` | Before claiming done or preparing commit |
| 8 | `requesting-code-review` | Milestone complete |
| 9 | `receiving-code-review` | Addressing review feedback |
| 10 | `finishing-a-development-branch` | All tasks done — merge/PR/cleanup options |

Also available: `dispatching-parallel-agents` (2+ independent tasks), `writing-skills` (authoring skills).

Commands: `/brainstorm`, `/write-plan`, `/execute-plan`. Subagent: `code-reviewer`.

## Project artifact paths

| Artifact | Path |
|----------|------|
| Design spec | `docs/superpowers/specs/YYYY-MM-DD-<topic>-design.md` |
| Implementation plan | `docs/superpowers/plans/YYYY-MM-DD-<feature>.md` |
| Git worktrees | `.worktrees/<branch>/` (gitignored) |

## Verification commands (evidence required)

| Check | Command |
|-------|---------|
| Unit tests | `flutter test` |
| Static analysis | `flutter analyze` |
| After Drift schema change | `flutter pub run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs` |
| Integration tests | `flutter test integration_test/` (device/emulator) |

Never claim tests pass or work is complete without **fresh command output** in the current session.

## Ramadan-specific constraints

- Drift migrations: bump `schemaVersion` in `app_database.dart`, update `onUpgrade`, then build_runner
- Release assets (`bundles_release/`, local `scripts/`) are gitignored — do not commit
- One focused feature per chat when possible
